T1  - Convertible bonds as backdoor equity financing
AU  - Stein, Jeremy C.
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
SP  - 3
EP  - 21
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/08/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(92)90022-P
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X9290022P
AB  - This paper argues that corporations may use convertible bonds as an indirect way to get equity into their capital structures when adverse-selection problems make a conventional stock issue unattractive. Unlike other theories of convertible bond issuance, the model here highlights: 1) the importance of call provisions on convertibles and 2) the significance of costs of financial distress to the information content of a convertible issue.
